article.headline: Winthrop 98, VMI 65
article.story: ROCK HILL, S.C. (AP) -- James Shuler scored 17 points and Torrell Martin and Michael Jenkins added 15 apiece to lead Winthrop to a 98-65 victory over VMI on Wednesday. The Eagles (15-6, 9-2 Big South Conference) shot 61 percent from the floor, never trailed and led 46-23 at halftime. Winthrop regained a share of first place in the conference with Birmingham Southern with the victory. The Keydets (7-15, 2-9) had 24 turnovers, and Winthrop scored 33 points off the miscues. Reggie Williams led VMI with 16 points. Fred Robinson added 12 points and Matt Murrer had 11. Williams hit a 3 with 11:16 to play in the first half to cut Winthrop's lead to 21-18, but the Eagles closed the half on a 25-8 run.
